<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-22T12:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-22T12:30:00-05:00" n="223" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/19<hi rend="superscript">12/14</hi>: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-22T14:00:00-03:30">October 22, 1940—2 p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October
                                        22—1:24 p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>241. Your 93, August 4, 3 p.m. Lieutenant Colonel Christian and
                                    Captain Brereton arrived this morning and we had a satisfactory
                                    preliminary meeting with the Minister for Foreign Affairs, the
                                    Minister of National Defense and the Inspector General of the
                                    Navy.</p>
                                <p>The conversations with officers of the Uruguayan Army and Navy
                                    will begin tomorrow morning.</p>
                                <p>Please advise General Strong.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>